                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14042306" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 24 Jun 2014 16:14:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Replaces use of IMCL in count and HH paging with a 1MB upper limit.  Most will be much less than this because they will hit the cell count limit first; for those that don&apos;t, 1MB is almost certainly better than 64.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14042307" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 24 Jun 2014 16:14:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=iamaleksey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;iamaleksey&quot;&gt;iamaleksey&lt;/a&gt; to review&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14042988" author="iamaleksey" created="Wed, 25 Jun 2014 02:49:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM, although not sure about the 1MB limit. It seems to be a rather arbitrary number (just like 64 used to be, I guess).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are you sure we should set it to 1, and not something in between 1 and the previous value? Maybe 4 or 8? Either way, +1 and go ahead with a limit you find reasonable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14042997" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 25 Jun 2014 03:14:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed w/ 4MB.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
